labor_categories.labor_category: Service and Installation Sheet Metal Worker

raw_data.title: Service and Installation Sheet Metal Worker
raw_data.description: Service and Installation Sheet Metal Worker fabricates, installs and maintains sheet-metal systems and fixtures.

raw_data.title: Facilities Maintenance Electronics Technician
raw_data.description: The Facilities Maintenance Electronics Technician must possess skills and experience (beyond the use of manuals), to operate, troubleshoot, repair, maintain and replace components for electronics. Skilled position requires expertise with electrical circuitry.

raw_data.title: Heavy Equipment Operator
raw_data.description: The Heavy Equipment Operator is responsible for the operation of a heavy equipment like a skid-steer loader to excavate, load or move dirt, gravel or snow. (Provision of heavy equipment can be added under OLM.)

raw_data.title: Delivery Driver
raw_data.description: The Delivery Driver directly supports a contract or project by transporting materials, tools and equipment to the job or project location. (Vehicles, equipment, tools, materials, are not included and must be added under OLM.)

raw_data.title: Grounds Maintenance Laborer and Driver
raw_data.description: The Grounds Maintenance Laborer and Driver maintains the grounds at commercial or government facilities, performs the same duties as the laborer, but also cleaning up  weeds, trash, debris from grounds and landscape, and from removal, sorting, properly disposing of them at landfill or recycling center. (The provision of a vehicle, materials and landfill disposal fees are not included and must be added under OLM)

raw_data.title: Grounds and Landscaping Supervisor
raw_data.description: The Grounds and Landscaping Supervisor is responsible for performing Grounds Maintenance  duties, and provides supervision, scheduling, quality control and other managerial duties. (Vehicles, equipment, tools, materials, paper products, etc. are not included and must be added under OLM.)

raw_data.title: Service and Installation Rigger
raw_data.description: The Service and Installation Rigger assembles rigging to lift and move equipment and material for a project or contract, safety hoisting, bracing, and lifting equipment. Expert understanding of safe use of equipment, OSHA training, acts as the “qualified person” to prepare JHA’s for the lift, and prepares and enforces lift plans, supervises lifts, and must be able to make adjustments in the field. (Does not include CRANE Operator.)

raw_data.title: Gardener
raw_data.description: The Gardener plans and executes small scale landscaping operations and maintains grounds and landscape of household, business and other properties, preparing and grading terrain, applying fertilizers, seeding and laying sod, and transplanting shrubs and plants, and cultivates them, using gardening implements and power-operated equipment. The Gardner plants new and repairs established lawns, garden beds, and other landscaping, locates and plants shrubs, trees, and flowers, mows and trims lawns, using hand or power mower, trims shrubs and cultivates gardens, sprays trees and shrubs and applies supplemental liquid and dry nutrients to lawn, trees and shrubs; cleans ground, using rakes, brooms, and hose, dig trenches and install drain tiles, repair concrete and asphalt walks and driveways',  (Vehicles, heavy equipment, machinery, tools, materials, chemicals, seed, plants, mulch, soil, tools, equipment, etc. are not included and must be added under OLM.) This employee has pesticide applicator license as required by the locality or contract, driver's license, horticultural certifications as required by contract

raw_data.title: Pest Controller
raw_data.description: The Pest Controller uses chemicals and traps to trap and/or kill pests that infest buildings and surrounding areas. Clean (Vehicles, equipment, traps, chemicals, etc. are not included and must be added under OLM.) Additional licenses may be required to handle pesticides.

raw_data.title: Accounting Clerk
raw_data.description: The Accounting Clerk performs billing and payment activities in support of a contract or project, tracking and categorizing costs, tracking project billing and project profitability, setting up jobs, assigning purchase orders, assisting with vendor invoices, preparing client invoices and statements, reporting to management on job progress and researching problems.

raw_data.title: Contract Administrator
raw_data.description: The Project Administrator is responsible for the administration of the contract or project, including taking phone calls, scheduling appointments, writing reports, training office staff, collecting data, contract deliverables, contract compliance, updating documents and plans and reporting.

labor_categories.labor_category: Facility Maintenance CMMS Operator and Production Analysis Technician

raw_data.title: Facility Maintenance CMMS Operator and Production Analysis Technician
raw_data.description: The Production Control Clerk has experience with Computerized Maintenance Management Systems (CMMS) and uses the system to receive, record, and assign work orders for routine, urgent and emergency repairs from the client; prepare and assign routine maintenance and tour work orders; work with other contract staff and subcontractors to record the resolution and notify the client; use the CMMS to prepare reports for contract management; and records information about the contract work such as the level of effort (times; production analysis, work quantity, etc.); and sort data for management use or client reports.

raw_data.title: Work Order Dispatcher
raw_data.description: Receive production paperwork for government projects or contracts such as work orders or daily reports, assembles for reports, closes tickets or reports to client, disseminates job assignments as directed by project manager or superintendent, keeps the schedule, requisitions materials as directed, assists project management team with other duties related to the performance and reporting of contract tasks.

raw_data.title: Collection Specialist
raw_data.description: The Collection Specialist is responsible for collection of delinquent accounts, works with project staff towards a resolution, assembles packages for claims and equitable adjustments, submits invoices in electronic billing systems, resolves issues to get invoices accepted and paid

raw_data.title: Project Superintendent
raw_data.description: The  Project Superintendent has a mastery of education and/or experience  required to supervise the field work by contractor staff and subcontractors,  on time, on budget and safely, for government projects awarded under the 03FAC schedule (i.e. SINs for complete facility maintenance, energy projects, HVACR maintenance, etc.)

raw_data.title: Project Estimator and/ or Manager
raw_data.description: The Project Estimator/ Manager has an expert combination of education and/or experience to prepare proposals and pricing for projects that will address the needs of facilities and buildings, and the ability and experience required to ensure successful completion and compliance of  contract requirements.

raw_data.title: Mechanical System Designer
raw_data.description: The Mechanical System Designer works with Mechanical Engineer to design mechanical systems and solicitations that are feasible to install and maintain for retrofits, upgrades, replacements, modernization and energy projects that can be fulfilled using  as the contractor's offerings under the 03FAC schedule (i.e. SINs for complete facility maintenance, energy projects, HVACR maintenance, etc.)
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: HVAC, Plumbing, or Electrical License Applicable

labor_categories.years_experience: HVAC, Plumbing, or Electrical License Applicable

raw_data.title: Safety Inspector
raw_data.description: The Safety Inspector is responsible for touring site and performing  Safety Inspections as required by contract, in accordance with the plans established in the project specifications. Certifications may include OSHA-10, OSHA-30CPR, etc.
raw_data.education_and_experience_substitution: Occupational Health & Safety Certification; BS in Occupational ESH; OSH certification

labor_categories.years_experience: Occupational Health & Safety Certification; BS in Occupational ESH; OSH certification

raw_data.title: Fire Watch/ Dedicated Safety Person
raw_data.description: The Fire Watch directly supports a contract or project by performing fire watch duties when the fire alarm systems are offline or during hazardous work (i.e. hot work, confined spaces, fall protection). Must have relevant OSHA training and certifications as required by contract or OSHA.

labor_categories.labor_category: Fire Watch/ Dedicated Safety Person After Regular Hours

raw_data.title: Fire Watch/ Dedicated Safety Person After Regular Hours
raw_data.description: The Fire Watch directly supports a contract or project by performing fire watch duties when the fire alarm systems are offline or during hazardous work (i.e. hot work, confined spaces, fall protection). Must have relevant OSHA training and certifications as required by contract or OSHA.

raw_data.title: Quality Control Manager/ Inspector
raw_data.description: The Quality Control Inspector is responsible for touring site and performing  QC Inspections as required by contract, in accordance with the QC plans established for the project specifications, work of contractor or subcontractors, or tour with government quality assurance personnel.  Must have certification required by contract (i.e. USACE CQM).
